rple Heart for wounds incurred in service. He attended Bowdoin College and lived most of his post-war life in New Hampshire. His military service continued the family pattern that included his grand-uncle William Adrian Ingersoll, USN paymaster, and Captain George Sumner Arnold, his paternal grandfather and commander of the New Haven Grays."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Woodbridge CT 1915 to Concord NH 2004","body":"Charles Ingersoll 'Ingy' Arnold was born July 14, 1915 in Woodbridge New Haven County Connecticut and died January 6, 2004 in Concord Merrimack County New Hampshire at age eighty-eight. He is buried at Old Hopkinton Cemetery Hopkinton New Hampshire. He married Dorothy Spoor of Pueblo Colorado in 1942 — she later served as Vice President of the Penny Pitou travel agency in Concord NH."}],"quotes":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"military_service":[{"war":"World War II","war_id":"WAR002","side":"American","rank_start":"2nd Lieutenant","rank_end":"2nd Lieutenant","unit":"United States Army","service_years":"WWII","awards":["Purple Heart"],"notes":"2nd Lieutenant United States Army during World War II. Recipient of the Purple Heart for wounds received in service."}],"education":[{"school_name":"Bowdoin College","role":"student","degree":"BA","graduation_year":1939,"notes":"Class of 1939; Alpha Delta Phi fraternity; first freshman to play on varsity hockey team; later honored 1992 as \"Number One Hockey Fan.\" Only one Hooker-tree person currently documented at Bowdoin so no INST entry per §9 2+ rule."},{"school_name":"Yale University School of Forestry","role":"student","degree":"Master of Forestry","graduation_year":1941,"notes":"M.F. 1941"}],"career":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Charles Ingersoll Arnold","first_name":"Charles","last_name":"Arnold","middle_name":"Ingersoll","married_names":[],"nickname":"Ingy","gender":"male"},"slug":"charles-arnold-1915"},"I01310":{"id":"I01310","former_id